            {
                "comment": "Amazing lecturer and cares about his students. His recorded lectures and notes are fantastic. Definitely recommend taking him!",
                "difficulty_rating": 1,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Great lecturer, his notes are incredibly detailed and neat which i love as even if you forget a concept it'll be right there for easy review. Exams weren't bad if you studied well. Lots of homework to be done but do them as they add up. Also, google him when he was young, you will not be disappointed ;) He actually cares about his students. Funny.",
                "difficulty_rating": 3,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "The lectures are long and a bit dry. The class is so large that I didn't really interact with him much, but he's a decent engineering professor. Make sure to take good notes, work on some of the homework after each lecture, and make sure your statics knowledge is fresh in your mind for this class.",
                "difficulty_rating": 4,
                "quality_rating": 3
            },
            {
                "comment": "I really enjoyed this course and it increased my interest in mechanical engineering. He is a very warm person who is also very funny. You could even say he is \"Based.\"\nI recommend attending all lectures, and doing the homework well because it is a clear indicator if you are ready for the test or not. ",
                "difficulty_rating": 3,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Blamed his students for a 50% average on his second midterm. Assigned way too much homework (13+ problems/week online, plus pre and post-discussion quizzes). Discussion attendance was essentially mandatory. Droned in lecture with no inflection in his voice. Did not seem interested in students comprehending the material.",
                "difficulty_rating": 5,
                "quality_rating": 2
            },
            {
                "comment": "Good lecturer, easy grader, helpful, and can be funny too. Not much more one can ask from just a really decent lecturer.",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Eriten is a solid choice for 306. He is very straight forward, lectures are easy to follow and not too boring considering the material. Take advantage of his office hours, he is actually a really nice guy. Tests can be difficult but if you study hard it will pay off. Really no complaints with him.",
                "difficulty_rating": 4,
                "quality_rating": 4
